benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from bundle

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios: TC01 (all fields), TC02 (single field), TC03 (multiple fields), TC04 (with optional headers), TC05 (no fields) cover core delete behavior.

Input Validation: TC06 (invalid bundleId format), TC09 (invalid customField UUID), TC19 (empty customField), TC22 (partial/trimmed bundleId), TC11 (extra query parameter, ignored), TC14 (header injection), TC08 (missing header)
gaps: Soft Deletes: no explicit test verifying soft-delete semantics or tombstone/flagged-deleted state (whether records are hard-deleted or can be recovered).
Rate Limiting: no tests for throttling or rate-limiting behavior.
Caching Behavior: no tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related caching behavior.
Authorization boundary detail: tests cover 401/400 scenarios, but no explicit test distinguishing 403 vs 401 in all contexts (may depend on system design).
Pagination: not applicable to DELETE, but no explicit tests around any related pagination behavior for GET after deletions (covered indirectly by TC25).
Edge-case coverage gaps: while many edge cases are covered (TC19, TC20, TC21, TC22), additional edge cases around extreme invalid inputs beyond those listed are not explored.
recommendations: Add a test to confirm soft-delete semantics or confirm that deletions are permanent (hard delete) and that a deleted flag or tombstone is used if applicable.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to verify behavior under bursty DELETE requests (e.g., N concurrent requests exceeding threshold).
Add tests to validate caching-related headers on DELETE responses if the API uses cache-control/ETag semantics.
Expand authorization tests to explicitly cover 403 Forbidden scenarios where a user lacks permissions, in addition to 401/400 cases.
Consider a test ensuring idempotency for repeated identical DELETE requests (beyond TC16) to confirm consistent behavior across repeated calls.
If applicable, add a test for extreme negative payloads or malformed header values beyond injection tests (e.g., special characters that could trigger parsing issues).
Maintain consistency with any soft-delete policy by adding a regression test that validates state after a sequence of deletes and re-reads.
